column1: 1285	"Question: Based on clues in the text
column2: why would farmers have appreciated cats eight thousand years ago?

column1: Choices: ['The cats were thought to be visiting goddesses.'
column2: 'The cats hunted and brought food to the farmers.'
column3: ""The cats helped keep the farmers' grain free of mice.""
column4: 'The cats helped farmers find better places to store grain.']

column1: Hint: Read the text about cats.
Cats are among the most popular pets in the world. Millions of people have welcomed cats into their homes. Indeed
column2: researchers believe that the relationship between cats and humans goes back to prehistoric times. But throughout history
column3: different cultures and people around the world have had different sentiments about cats. Such feelings have ranged from fear to worship.

column1: People probably first developed friendly relationships with cats around eight thousand years ago
column2: when farming and agriculture had just started to develop in the Middle East. Farmers were growing and storing grain
column3: which in turn attracted mice and other pests. Cats were wild then. However
column4: they were likely drawn to farming communities because there were mice to hunt. The farmers would have noticed and appreciated these visitors. To keep the cats around
column5: these early farmers may have given food and even shelter to the wild cats. The farmers and cats probably helped one another.

column1: It wasn't until five thousand years later that the Egyptians started to treat cats as pets. Cats in ancient Egypt were not simply valued
column3: many Egyptian goddesses took the form of cats. People who were caught harming cats were punished severely. Some cats were even made into mummies when they died. Normally
